{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/path\/init(ellipsein:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path\/init(ellipseIn:)"},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates a path as an ellipse within the given rectangle.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"ellipseIn"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"rect"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGRect","text":"CGRect"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The rectangle that bounds the ellipse."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"rect"}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a convenience function that creates a path of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ellipse. Using this convenience function is more efficient than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"creating a path and adding an ellipse to it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ellipse is approximated by a sequence of Bézier","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"curves. Its center is the midpoint of the rectangle defined by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the rect parameter. If the rectangle is square, then the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ellipse is circular with a radius equal to one-half the width","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(or height) of the rectangle. If the rect parameter specifies a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rectangular shape, then the major and minor axes of the ellipse","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are defined by the width and height of the rectangle.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The ellipse forms a complete subpath of the path—that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is, the ellipse drawing starts with a move-to operation and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ends with a close-subpath operation, with all moves oriented in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the clockwise direction. If you supply an affine transform,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then the constructed Bézier curves that define the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ellipse are transformed before they are added to the path."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"init","title":"init(ellipseIn:)","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"ellipseIn"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CGRect","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGRect"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"roleHeading":"Initializer","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/Path.swift#L253","fileName":"Path.swift"},"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4PathV9ellipseInACSo6CGRectV_tcfc"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Path/init(ellipseIn:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"ellipseIn","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGRect","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGRect"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"title":"init(ellipseIn:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path\/init(ellipseIn:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a path as an ellipse within the given rectangle."}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/path\/init(ellipsein:)"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","role":"collection","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}],"title":"OpenSwiftUI"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Path":{"title":"Path","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The outline of a 2D shape."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Path","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Path","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/path","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path"}}}